In article <TODD.92Dec30124821@palomar.tivoli.com> todd@palomar.tivoli.com writes:
  [ hash functions like MD5 are exportable, encryption functions are not ]
> Isn't it a simple matter to use an algorithm like MD5 to produce a
> very strong cipher?

Yes. This is exactly what motivated me to write ``snuffle'', which builds
an encryptor out of Merkle's Snefru hash function. For several months now
I've been working with NSA and the State Department to see if I can export
the (one-page) snuffle code.

---Dan
